      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PIQUE (3) atoned for a narrow fresh defeat when she led to salute last start at Ballarat, getting home by 1.3 metres. Draws to push forward again and has upside so she is capable of getting the job done again. ASPEN BELLE (6) was a big improver in her second outing when she came from the back line and scored by a head at Charlton. Looks to have ability and could go through her grades. ARGYLE MUSE (4) will be fitter for recent racing and is in the mix following a solid fifth at her most recent appearance at Ballarat. THE FASHIONISTA (5) bombed the start last time but there was some merit in her other two outings this time in and her lone career win came at this distance.",
